reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Lamp Overall
reviews.reviewText: It's a nifty little desk lamp - and just that: A desk lamp. It's not bright enough to effectively illuminate a room, but great for those who just want to read, see what's on a desk or otherwise. Because it's a touch sensor lamp, it will not work with your typical light switch which is a bit of an inconvenience when entering a dark room. Still, it's a very nice looking lamp, and the 2 USB ports allow for convenient phone/tablet charging and saves up cord/socket space, so that's definitely a plus.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easiest Lamp To Turn On
reviews.reviewText: I love this lamp! At first, I didn't think it was anything special, just a desk lamp with a traditional look. The best part is it's so easy to turn on and off. All you have to do is tap the lamp anywhere on the stem or base and it lights up. There's no looking for switches or knobs, just tap the lamp to go on and tap it again to go off. It also has 3 different lighting levels - your choice whether you choose dim, a little brighter or the brightest. Definitely worth the price! :-)
